<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-02-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-02-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="238" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d238">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hart</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-02-08"><hi rend="italic">February 8,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay directs Mr. Hart, if the facts are as represented in
                            Department’s telegram of January 22 last, to make firm demand, as
                            instructed, without specifying amount of indemnity, which depends upon
                            further investigation.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>